{
  "doc_id": "2445",
  "text": "In the analyses, studies were weighted according to the inverse variance of the regression coefficient, and the weighted regression coefficients were combined assuming a fixed effect model. An alternative approach, assuming a random effects model, was evaluated and this revealed the same results. For reports where the variance was not reported, the variance of each study was calculated by deriving the standard error from the reported 95% CI. [CITATION_1] Separate analyses were performed including the crudest and the most adjusted estimate from each report.",
